At least, thirty people were killed on Friday when suspected bandits attacked Tsauwa and Dankar villages in Batsari Local Government Area of Katsina State. About twenty-one people, majority of whom were old people and children were killed in Tsauwa Houses, animals, and foodstuffs were razed in the attack. ALSO READ: Unemployment: Buhari orders review of varsity’s curriculum Armed herdsmen in Army uniform kill eight in Delta… Nigerian youths best vanguard to tackle corruption ― NYSC DG… Bayelsa: Wike demands resignation of Oshiomhole over failure… PDP will take over Lagos come 2023 ― Ex-party boss, Selleh On Saturday, the Katsina State Police Commissioner, Sanusi Buba, was visited the two communities for an on-the-spot assessment of the damage done during the attack. The police chief who confirmed that thirty people were killed by the bandits said, “I still find it surprising that whatever could have been the motive, these people ( suspected bandits) could still carry out these dastardly acts. We are, however, after them. “Twenty-one people were killed in Tsauwa while nine were killed in Dankar.” Tribune Online observed that security in the two villages has been beefed up in the aftermath of the attack. Security personnel including police and the army as well as local vigilantes were sighted at different positions in the two villages on Saturday evening. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE TO GET IT!!! STAY STRONGER, LONGER AND SATISFY MADAM LIKE NEVER BEFORE WITH THIS NATURAL SUPPLEMENTS WITH NO SIDE EFFECTS. CLICK NOW. CLICK HERE NOW TO WORK FROM HOME ENTIRELY AT YOUR OWN CONVINIENCE AND GET PAID WEEKLY, DIRECTLY INTO YOUR SPECIFIED BANK ACCOUNT.REGISTRATION IS ABSOLUTELY FREE.